The paper deals with pattern mining, which is a subfield of data mining and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on nonmonotonic constraints for pattern selection and applies them to interval tuple datasets. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.IR (information retrieval). Among these, cs.DB and cs.DM are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with data mining and pattern mining, which are closely related to databases and discrete mathematics. However, the paper also introduces a new algorithm for efficient pattern generation, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
